        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 28 at 1:54PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 153 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
North Bend State Park, or 8 miles west of Harrisville, moving east at
50 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
North Bend State Park, Cairo, Pennsboro, Pike, Nutter Farm, Berea,
Pullman, Harrisville, Petroleum, Highland, and Ellenboro.

This includes Route 50 in West Virginia between mile markers 27 and
43.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
